title: KeyScrambler Premium 3.4.0.4 [ENG] [Serial]
description:
KeyScrambler bypasses most standard keyloggers by encrypting keystrokes. However, it does not detect keyloggers, including the type that steal screenshots or turns on webcams. Nevertheless, KeyScrambler can provide protection during email, VoIP and online gaming conversations. Recent news articles and security recommendations suggest that it's best to use encryption methods provided by anti-keylogger software to secure your online communications. This TopTenREVIEWS Bronze Award winning software can even add an extra layer of security by providing safe transfers of login information via password managers.

While we are used to people viewing our social media accounts, there are still some things we would like to keep private, including our Skype conversations, chat interactions, passwords, emails and personal information. KeyScrambler protects these types of interactions. This software also helps protect your ID by securing entries into tax software and personal finance applications. It also secures small business accounting software, including QuickBooks.

This keystroke encryption software supports most browsers, including Firefox, Google Chrome, Safari and Internet Explorer. In addition, it is compatible with less common browsers such as Opera, RocketMelt, CometBird and Pale Moon. It can also encrypt most types of emails, including Outlook, Thunderbird, Eudora, The Bat! and Windows Mail.

This software secures your interactions with strangers during such activities as online gaming and chats. Popular games KeyScrambler protects include "World of Warcraft," "Diablo," "EverQuest" and "StarCraft." Numerous poker apps are protected as well, such as "Full Tilt Poker," "PartyPoker" and "Titan Poker." Chat and VoIP conversations this anti-keylogger protects include ICQ, Live Messenger, Skype, Yahoo and Google Hangouts.

KeyScrambler protects your logins, passwords and online communications using powerful Blowfish 128-bit symmetric and RSA 1024-bit encryption methods. It is compatible with hundreds of applications and the newest Windows operating systems, including 64-bit versions of Windows. We especially recommend this software if you use a password manager to provide extra security for all your login info.
